            "id": "4579249",
            "title": "Pony AI gains after updating on its robotaxi progress",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Pony AI (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PONY\" title=\"Pony AI Inc.\">PONY</a></span>) used the Auto China 2026 conference in Beijing to highlight the company's stronger push toward large-scale commercialization of its autonomous driving business, led by lower-cost Gen-7 robotaxis, fleet expansion, and a more efficient AI training system. Notably, the company highlighted that the total cost of its 2027 robotaxi in China, including the base vehicle and autonomous driving kit, is expected to fall below RMB230K while its fleet has grown to 1,400 vehicles from 270 and user registrations have surpassed 1M.</p>\n<p>In terms of profitability, the company noted that its Gen-7 kit has delivered a 70% reduction in bill-of-materials costs, helping it reach unit-economics breakeven in two major Southern China markets. Pony AI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PONY\" title=\"Pony AI Inc.\">PONY</a>) said it plans to expand the fleet to more than 3K robotaxis by the end of this year and grow to 20 cities globally, with nearly half overseas, while also preparing an international version of its Gen-7 platform for local market requirements.</p>\n<p>\"Today, the question is no longer whether Robotaxi can work. The focus is on how to scale it safely, efficiently, and at the right cost,\" updated Pony AI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PONY\" title=\"Pony AI Inc.\">PONY</a>) CEO Dr. James Peng.</p>\n<p>Shares of Pony AI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/PONY\" title=\"Pony AI Inc.\">PONY</a>) were up 2% in premarket action.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
